				                <div>Hello Ness,<br />
<br />
Thank you for your question. Your issue does not seem to be related to updates KB2837618 or KB2837643.<br />
<br />
Since IMAP accesses emails on the server, what you are seeing on your <strong>PC desktop</strong> is what is currently on the server. It should save your <em>Sent</em> mail as well, if not make sure you are <a href="http://www.inmotionhosting.com/support/email/outlook/inbox-subscribe">subscribed to your IMAP folder</a>.<br />
<br />
I would then check if you are using <em>IMAP</em> or <em>POP</em> on the <strong>Mac</strong>. Since you are only seeing older emails on the Mac, they may have been downloaded via POP, and are now stored on the Mac. <br />
<br />
If they have been downloaded to the Mac via POP, you will have to export them, and then Import them into the PC computer. How this is accomplished depends on your specific email clients, for example Mac Mail, Thunderbird or Outlook.<br />
<br />
If you have any further questions, feel free to post them below.<br />
Thank you,<br />
<br />
-John-Paul</div>
