						<div style='float:right;margin:0px 0px 15px 15px;font-size:12px;color:#aaa'>2014-07-16 5:14 pm</div>
				                <div>Hello Julie,<br />
<br />
I'm sorry to hear that you're having problems with email.  This kind of problem is often related to two types of email protocols being used.  One could be IMAP, while your phone is using POP3.  POP3 Downloads the files from the server.  So, if the files are there, they may be there until the phone syncs, and then the files are no longer on the server, but on your phone.  The best way to resolve this would be to change the phone to use IMAP (or at least make sure that it does).  If all devices are using IMAP that is attaching to the account, then the emails shouldn't disappear.  If you require further assistance, please provide us a domain name and the steps duplicate the problem so that we may investigate the issue further.<br />
<br />
Regards,<br />
Arnel C.</div>
