						<div style='float:right;margin:0px 0px 15px 15px;font-size:12px;color:#aaa'>2015-01-28 10:27 am</div>
				                <div>Hello Ecm,<br />
<br />
Thanks for the question.  If you are using two different email clients connected to the same email account and one uses POP3 while the other uses IMAP, then yes you will have a problem with retaining some of your emails.  The POP3 client works by downloading emails into the INBOX folder.  Depending on the configuration, the emails may actually be downloading TO your computer and off of the server.  So, if you have your POP3 email client doing that, then there would be no emails retained that IMAP client could actually see.   I would recommend changing your POP3 client over to IMAP, then it will not be a problem as the emails are retained on the server.<br />
<br />
I hope this helps to answer your question, please let us know if you require any further  assistance.</div>
